      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARIS PARTY (1) flew the lids with a fast early split last time, hitting the frame with a 5 length second (20.15) over 350m at Goulburn and making it two placings on end. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Can find winning form. GORGEOUS GOSSIP (7) settled well back early on debut and always towards the tail to finish sixth (19.07) at this track over 320m. Much improved and rates a winning chance. UTAH JAN (8) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at Gosford over 388m behind Hands On Tina (23.47) in a Maiden. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Should be about the money. ONLY RUMOURS (6) will be thereabouts while fresh.",
